{
  "texts": [
    "Overfitting is commonly caused by limited training data, while shallow network layers may not extract enough high-level information.",
    "Nonetheless, deep networks face issues such as gradient disappearance, which can compromise the benefits of increasing the network depth.In order to address this issue, the ResNet network is utilized in this paper as the foundational network, which was introduced in 2015 and is based on a residual structure as its core module.",
    "The residual learning unit, as depicted in Fig. 3, consists of multiple convolutional layers and skip connections.",
    "It effectively transforms the input features into output features while maintaining consistency.",
    "The following are the definitions of its components.γ = σ (F(X) + X) (1)F(X) = W 2 σ (W 1 X) (2)where γ is the output, and X is the input."
  ]
}